Pre-Game Insights: This article is more than 2 months old
LA Dodgers roar back from five runs down to win World Series over New York Yankees
Freddie Freeman celebrated their win against the New York Yankees in Game 5 to win the baseball World Series!
If you grew up in a house with a Brooklyn Dodgers fan like I did, you understand the significance of a Dodgers team winning a title inside the five boroughs.
Post-Match Reflections: The Dodgers have won the World Series!!
The Yankees completely fell apart, committing mental error after mental error in a ghastly performance that showed exactly what they are, which is a team that wasn’t true World Series caliber.
LA celebrate a non-shortened season title for the first time since 1988. Yes, they have a loaded roster, but they’re an extraordinary club who deserve to be champs.
Manager Dave Roberts has come a very long way – he was tremendous pulling the strings for the Dodgers in this series.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers are champions for an eighth time in franchise history. And it’s the fourth time they have beaten New York in doing so.
The Dodgers have completed the biggest comeback in a World Series clinching victory.
The Yankees have committed three errors tonight and that doesn’t even come close to telling the story of the shoddiest play I’ve ever seen from a World Series team.
